Democrat, Joe Biden, took the lead in key battleground state of.Pennsylvania on Friday, where a victory for the former Vice President would push him past the threshold of electoral votes needed to win the White House, official data showed. According to AFP, more ballots are yet to be counted, but shortly before 1400 GMT, Biden had moved ahead of incumbent President, Donald Trump, by more than 5,500 votes, according to official provisional results from the state government.  See Also






